e harsher punishments for serious violent crimes while encouraging positive, non-punitive interventions in less serious cases, its impact on the youth justice system remains controversial.Implementing and Working with the Youth Criminal Justice Act across Canada provides the first comprehensive, province-by-province analysis of how each Canadian jurisdiction has implemented the Act in accordance with its own history, traditions, and institutional arrangements. Drawing on in-depth interviews with probation officers, counselors, educators, and social workers, the contributors use the experiences of practitioners to offer a new analytical perspective on a complicated and contentious aspect of the Canadian justice system. Their conclusions provide vital policy and program information for researchers, practitioners, and policy makers concerned with Canada’s youth justice systems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aJuvenile justice, Administration ofzCanadaxProvinces. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aAlain, Marc , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAlain, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBell, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Kathryn M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorrado, Raymond R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorrado, Raymond R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDesrosiers, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDyck, Murray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEnström, Malin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGronsdahl, Karla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHam